<div id="review_526194861" class="review nosyndicate" itemprop="reviews" itemscope itemtype="http://schema.org/Review">
  <link itemprop="url" href="https://www.goodreads.com/review/show/526194861" />
    <a title="Darlene Breeden" class="left imgcol" href="/user/show/3327618-darlene-breeden"><img alt="Darlene Breeden" src="https://images.gr-assets.com/users/1266856026p2/3327618.jpg" /></a>

  <div class="left bodycol">
    <div class="reviewHeader uitext stacked">
        <a class="reviewDate createdAt right" href="/review/show/526194861?book_show_action=true">Feb 04, 2013</a>

      <span itemprop="author" itemscope itemtype="http://schema.org/Person">
        <a title="Darlene Breeden" class="user" itemprop="url" name="Darlene Breeden" href="/user/show/3327618-darlene-breeden">Darlene Breeden</a>
      </span>

        rated it
        <span class=" staticStars notranslate" title="really liked it"><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10">really liked it</span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p0"></span></span>



        

    </div>


        <div class="reviewText stacked">
              <span id="reviewTextContainer526194861" class="readable"
              >
            
<span id="freeTextContainer13613957440429435829">Though I typically do not read historical romance books, Kate Worth&apos;s debut novel, The Promise, turned out to be a refreshing change from what is usually found in the genre. <br/><br/>Along with the building passion and love between the heroine and hero, this novel provides so much more ~ it is an intriguing storyline involving a strong heroine who is committed to doing the right thing for someone she loves, even at her own personal detriment. While she is beautiful, in her own way, it is her inner streng</span>
  <span id="freeText13613957440429435829" style="display:none">Though I typically do not read historical romance books, Kate Worth's debut novel, The Promise, turned out to be a refreshing change from what is usually found in the genre. <br /><br />Along with the building passion and love between the heroine and hero, this novel provides so much more ~ it is an intriguing storyline involving a strong heroine who is committed to doing the right thing for someone she loves, even at her own personal detriment. While she is beautiful, in her own way, it is her inner strength and courage that makes her truly beautiful. She is loyal above all else. <br /><br />I found all the characters to be interesting and unique, and the dialogue, while timely to its setting, still felt modern. It flowed so easily, never missing a beat. That was an added bonus for me.<br /><br />No matter what your reading preference, I think everyone can find something in this book to love, so I highly recommend The Promise.<br /><br /> </span>
  <a data-text-id="13613957440429435829" href="#" onclick="swapContent($(this));; return false;">...more</a>

          </span>
        </div>


