<div id="review_406506721" class="review nosyndicate" itemprop="reviews" itemscope itemtype="http://schema.org/Review">
  <link itemprop="url" href="https://www.goodreads.com/review/show/406506721" />
    <a title="Tina" class="left imgcol" href="/user/show/5074703-tina"><img alt="Tina" src="https://images.gr-assets.com/users/1543350884p2/5074703.jpg" /></a>

  <div class="left bodycol">
    <div class="reviewHeader uitext stacked">
        <a class="reviewDate createdAt right" href="/review/show/406506721?book_show_action=true">Sep 03, 2012</a>

      <span itemprop="author" itemscope itemtype="http://schema.org/Person">
        <a title="Tina" class="user" itemprop="url" name="Tina" href="/user/show/5074703-tina">Tina</a>
      </span>

        rated it
        <span class=" staticStars notranslate" title="it was amazing"><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10">it was amazing</span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span></span>



        

          <div class="uitext greyText bookshelves">
            Shelves:
              <a class="actionLinkLite" href="/review/list/5074703-tina?shelf=dukes-lords-lady">dukes-lords-lady</a>, 
              <a class="actionLinkLite" href="/review/list/5074703-tina?shelf=kate-worth">kate-worth</a>
          </div>
    </div>


        <div class="reviewText stacked">
              <span id="reviewTextContainer406506721" class="readable"
              >
            
<span id="freeTextContainer5799909111193087007">I was totally captivated by this story. The author weaves a story that enthralls the reader from page one and never lets up until the end. The author transported me from the 21st century to an era where Lords, Ladies, and Dukes rule the day.<br/><br/>I must confess that this book had 2 elements that I tend to shy away from in my readings: a virgin and children (where the story centers on them). In other words, if the story has virgins + children= me not reading. Well as I stated earlier this book had both</span>
  <span id="freeText5799909111193087007" style="display:none">I was totally captivated by this story. The author weaves a story that enthralls the reader from page one and never lets up until the end. The author transported me from the 21st century to an era where Lords, Ladies, and Dukes rule the day.<br /><br />I must confess that this book had 2 elements that I tend to shy away from in my readings: a virgin and children (where the story centers on them). In other words, if the story has virgins + children= me not reading. Well as I stated earlier this book had both. However, to the testament of the author's writing ability, these elements did not take away from my enjoyment of the story. The virgin element was not a big piece of the story but when the time came it was written beautifully. I had to remind myself that the story takes place in a different time when married couples kept separate bedrooms. As far as the children element, there is only one child who is a big part of the story. Once again the author did a great job of not overwhelming the reader with scenes involving the child. For me this was important.<br /><br />The story was about love but had elements of intrigue. I liked everything about this book and look forward to reading more by this author.<br /></span>
  <a data-text-id="5799909111193087007" href="#" onclick="swapContent($(this));; return false;">...more</a>

          </span>
        </div>


