<div id="review_378490204" class="review" itemprop="reviews" itemscope itemtype="http://schema.org/Review">
  <link itemprop="url" href="https://www.goodreads.com/review/show/378490204" />
    <a title="Kathy Andrews" class="left imgcol" href="/user/show/3437146-kathy-andrews"><img alt="Kathy Andrews" src="https://images.gr-assets.com/users/1268602529p2/3437146.jpg" /></a>

  <div class="left bodycol">
    <div class="reviewHeader uitext stacked">
        <a class="reviewDate createdAt right" href="/review/show/378490204?book_show_action=true">Jul 27, 2012</a>

      <span itemprop="author" itemscope itemtype="http://schema.org/Person">
        <a title="Kathy Andrews" class="user" itemprop="url" name="Kathy Andrews" href="/user/show/3437146-kathy-andrews">Kathy Andrews</a>
      </span>

        rated it
        <span class=" staticStars notranslate" title="it was amazing"><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10">it was amazing</span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span></span>

          <span class="greyText">&nbsp;&middot;&nbsp;</span>
          <a class="lightGreyText" title="ebook 9781476274669" href="/book/show/15758934-the-promise">review of another edition</a>


        

    </div>


        <div class="reviewText stacked">
              <span id="reviewTextContainer378490204" class="readable"
              >
            
<span id="freeTextContainer5520444540539647954">Even in fiction rarely do I find a man for whom I am willing to give up my independent lifestyle. Finn is the type of hero whom I would love to swoon in his arms and share a lifetime with. It is an added bonus that he is independently wealthy with a full staff to take care of the cooking and cleaning for him and our time would be our own to do with as we please. The lead female character is also someone whom I would enjoy as a best friend forever - sweet without being weak, smart without being a</span>
  <span id="freeText5520444540539647954" style="display:none">Even in fiction rarely do I find a man for whom I am willing to give up my independent lifestyle. Finn is the type of hero whom I would love to swoon in his arms and share a lifetime with. It is an added bonus that he is independently wealthy with a full staff to take care of the cooking and cleaning for him and our time would be our own to do with as we please. The lead female character is also someone whom I would enjoy as a best friend forever - sweet without being weak, smart without being arrogant, capable without being overbearing. The antagonist is a person whom I could despise completely. It is refreshing that the bad guy did not dominate the storyline, but yet there was hardship to overcome so the story was not too good to be true. Nice job Kate! I cannot wait for your next book.</span>
  <a data-text-id="5520444540539647954" href="#" onclick="swapContent($(this));; return false;">...more</a>

          </span>
        </div>


