<div id="review_371773022" class="review nosyndicate" itemprop="reviews" itemscope itemtype="http://schema.org/Review">
  <link itemprop="url" href="https://www.goodreads.com/review/show/371773022" />
    <a title="Mandy" class="left imgcol" href="/user/show/4874444-mandy"><img alt="Mandy" src="https://images.gr-assets.com/users/1625616321p2/4874444.jpg" /></a>

  <div class="left bodycol">
    <div class="reviewHeader uitext stacked">
        <a class="reviewDate createdAt right" href="/review/show/371773022?book_show_action=true">Jul 18, 2012</a>

      <span itemprop="author" itemscope itemtype="http://schema.org/Person">
        <a title="Mandy" class="user" itemprop="url" name="Mandy" href="/user/show/4874444-mandy">Mandy</a>
      </span>

        rated it
        <span class=" staticStars notranslate" title="really liked it"><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10">really liked it</span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p0"></span></span>

          <span class="greyText">&nbsp;&middot;&nbsp;</span>
          <a class="lightGreyText" title="ebook 9781476274669" href="/book/show/15758934-the-promise">review of another edition</a>


        

          <div class="uitext greyText bookshelves">
            Shelves:
              <a class="actionLinkLite" href="/review/list/4874444-mandy?shelf=historical-romance">historical-romance</a>
          </div>
    </div>


        <div class="reviewText stacked">
              <span id="reviewTextContainer371773022" class="readable"
              >
            
<span id="freeTextContainer2982845640361275719">&quot;The Promise&quot; is a typical historical romance, but is written better than many, and the plot is not one that feels as if it has been done before. There was nothing cheesy in it that made me roll my eyes as I often find in this genre. The plot is well-developed, original, and believable, and I love how the author ties everything together. The characters are well-fleshed out and distinguishable, from the main characters Jane and Finn, his moody older brother Cam, to the butler Peckham, and the vil</span>
  <span id="freeText2982845640361275719" style="display:none">"The Promise" is a typical historical romance, but is written better than many, and the plot is not one that feels as if it has been done before. There was nothing cheesy in it that made me roll my eyes as I often find in this genre. The plot is well-developed, original, and believable, and I love how the author ties everything together. The characters are well-fleshed out and distinguishable, from the main characters Jane and Finn, his moody older brother Cam, to the butler Peckham, and the villain, Thomas, who is completely heartless. Historical events are well-researched and accurate, and I loved spending a little time in 19th Century England.<br /><br />Definitely recommend this book to anyone who likes this genre, or I think it would be an excellent one to start with if you are wanting to try it for the first time. Excellent debut novel!</span>
  <a data-text-id="2982845640361275719" href="#" onclick="swapContent($(this));; return false;">...more</a>

          </span>
        </div>


